## D19 API Source Configuration
**Status:** draft
**Module:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs`
**Depends on:** G13

```rust
pub struct ApiSource {
    pub id: String,
    pub name: String,
    pub provider: Provider,
    pub api_key_env: String,
    pub api_key_stored: Option<String>,
    pub base_url: Option<String>,
    pub is_available: bool,
    pub models: Vec<ModelDefinition>,
}

pub struct ModelDefinition {
    pub id: String,
    pub name: String,
    pub tier: ModelTier,
}

pub enum ModelTier { Light, Mid, Heavy }

// CRUD + detection
pub fn load_api_sources() -> Vec<ApiSource>
pub fn save_api_sources(sources: &[ApiSource]) -> Result<(), ConfigError>
pub fn detect_available_providers() -> Vec<ApiSource>

// Per-source operations
pub fn resolve_api_key(source: &ApiSource) -> Option<String>
pub async fn test_connection(source: &ApiSource, model: &str) -> Result<ConnectionTestResult, ConfigError>
```

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Unconfigured: First startup
    Unconfigured --> Detecting: auto-detect triggered
    Detecting --> Detected: keys/env found
    Detecting --> Empty: nothing found
    Detected --> Configured: user saves
    Empty --> Configured: user adds source manually
    Configured --> Testing: test_connection()
    Testing --> Available: connection OK
    Testing --> Unavailable: connection failed
    Available --> Configured: edit
    Unavailable --> Configured: fix and retry
    Configured --> [*]
```

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `String` | Unique identifier (e.g., "anthropic-primary") |
| `name` | `String` | Human-readable display name |
| `provider` | `Provider` | Anthropic, OpenAI, or Local{url} |
| `api_key_env` | `String` | Env var name or "settings:KEY" for ~/.claude |
| `api_key_stored` | `Option<String>` | Base64-obfuscated key |
| `base_url` | `Option<String>` | Custom endpoint (proxies, local) |
| `is_available` | `bool` | Startup detection result |
| `models` | `Vec<ModelDefinition>` | Available models with tier labels |

```
fn detect_available_providers():
    sources = []

    // 1. Check ~/.claude/settings.json for Anthropic key
    if settings.env has ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN or ANTHROPIC_API_KEY:
        sources.push(ApiSource {
            provider: Anthropic,
            models: [
                ModelDefinition { id: "claude-3-5-haiku-20241022", tier: Light },
                ModelDefinition { id: "claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022", tier: Mid },
                ModelDefinition { id: "claude-3-opus-20240229", tier: Heavy },
            ],
            is_available: true,
        })

    // 2. Check OPENAI_API_KEY env var
    if env has OPENAI_API_KEY:
        sources.push(ApiSource {
            provider: OpenAI,
            models: [
                ModelDefinition { id: "gpt-4o-mini", tier: Light },
                ModelDefinition { id: "gpt-4o", tier: Mid },
                ModelDefinition { id: "o1", tier: Heavy },
            ],
            is_available: true,
        })

    // 3. Check localhost:11434 for Ollama
    if http://localhost:11434/api/tags responds:
        sources.push(ApiSource {
            provider: Local { url: "http://localhost:11434" },
            models: fetch from /api/tags,
            is_available: true,
        })

    return sources

fn resolve_api_key(source):
    if source.api_key_env starts with "settings:":
        return read ~/.claude/settings.json -> env[key]
    if env has source.api_key_env:
        return env[source.api_key_env]
    if source.api_key_stored is Some:
        return base64_decode(source.api_key_stored)
    return None
```


| Tier | Anthropic | OpenAI | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| Light | claude-3-5-haiku | gpt-4o-mini | Routing, test gen, docs |
| Mid | claude-3-5-sonnet | gpt-4o | Planning, coding |
| Heavy | claude-3-opus | o1 | Architecture, review |



| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/forge/config/api-sources` | List all sources |
| POST | `/api/forge/config/api-sources` | Create source |
| PUT | `/api/forge/config/api-sources/{id}` | Update source |
| DELETE | `/api/forge/config/api-sources/{id}` | Delete source |
| POST | `/api/forge/config/api-sources/{id}/test` | Test connectivity |



