```


```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Loading: mount
    Loading --> Ready: editor initialized
    Ready --> Editing: user types
    Editing --> Editing: input
    Editing --> SlashMenuOpen: type '/'
    SlashMenuOpen --> Editing: select item or Esc
    Editing --> BubbleMenuOpen: text selected
    BubbleMenuOpen --> Editing: apply format or blur
    Editing --> Dragging: drag handle engaged
    Dragging --> Ready: drop completes
    Editing --> Saving: Ctrl+S
    Saving --> Ready: emit save event
    Ready --> [*]: unmount
```


| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `editor` | `Editor` | Tiptap Editor instance (ProseMirror wrapper) |
| `doc` | `JSONContent` | ProseMirror document tree (internal source of truth) |
| `markdown` | `string` | Serialized persistence format |
| `slashQuery` | `string` | Current filter text after '/' |
| `slashRange` | `Range` | ProseMirror selection range when '/' triggered |
| `bubbleVisible` | `boolean` | Whether bubble menu should render |


```
fn onUpdate({ editor }):
    markdown = editor.storage.markdown.getMarkdown()
    emit('update', markdown)

fn onSlashTrigger({ query, range }):
    slashQuery = query
    slashRange = range
    slashItems = filter(allSlashItems, query)
    slashMenuOpen = true

fn onSlashSelect(item):
    editor.chain().focus().deleteRange(slashRange).run()
    item.command({ editor, range: slashRange })
    slashMenuOpen = false

fn onKeydown(event):
    if event.key == 'Mod-s':
        event.preventDefault()
        emit('save', editor.storage.markdown.getMarkdown())
    if event.key == 'Mod-a':
        // Notion-style: first press selects node, second selects all
        if not selectionCoversFullNode:
            editor.commands.selectTextWithinNodeBoundaries()
            event.preventDefault()
```

